            <thetext>qx.Class has a lot of dependencies and with that, a lot of code size (see qx.Server with basically only qx.Class and almoste 50kb min + gzip). This is way too much for a lightweight library like qx.Website which is why we used qx.Bootstrap instead for the website branch of qooxdoo. Having those two conecpts in one framework is not a good situation if you have to maintain the project. So the basic idea behind this task is to check if its possible to reduce the dependencies of qx.Class so we can use qx.Class in qx.Website and with that, continue the process of unifying the widget sets.</thetext>
